This should be fixed with the update to the secondary/supplementary relabeling (version >0.19.3).

The reason this can happen is when there is more than 1 valid alignment (primary and a secondary), but the secondary has a slightly higher AS (alignment score) so it gets sorted before the primary.
Raptor 0.19.3 used to assign the primary flag to the alignment with "path_id = 0" and all others would be secondary. Sorting wouldn't impact the primary label in this case.
